CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, October 4, 1958, pg. 1 reads: "They Have Sky for Roof - This will happen soon for the family of Mrs. Jesse Salik, who is shown with two of her seven children in front of the remaining double apartment which the family currently occupies in Ingram Palace, while a re-development crew tears the roof off the rest of the building. Suitable living quarters, into which the Saliks can move, are not yet available. - Harris Photos."
TitMainTitle: Two women, including Jesse Salik, and three children, two playing with hula hoops, gathered on lawn outside of row house in Ingram Palace housing project, with right side of building being demolished for redevelopment, Ingram, Pennsylvania
